{
  "texts": [
    "Unsurprisingly, ReInfoSelect (Conv-KNRM) and ReInfoSelect (BERT) performed slightly better than BM25.",
    "BERT for Balancing Effectiveness and EfficiencyBERT models are more effective than previously proposed neural network ranking models in terms of document retrieval.",
    "However, BERT Base has 110 million parameters and BERT Large has 340 million parameters.",
    "Therefore, if the query and the text are fed simultaneously into BERT, its computational complexity is high, leading to a long computation time.",
    "To eliminate this deficiency, researchers have focused on two aspects: 1) reducing the interaction time between the query and the document, i.e., through dual-encoder-based models, and 2) reducing the number of hyperparameters of BERT, i.e., through distillation models."
  ]
}